{
  "buildCommand": "npm run build",
  "outputDirectory": "dist",
  "rewrites": [{ "source": "/((?!api/).*)", "destination": "/index.html" }]
}
```

That replaces what `netlify.toml` was doing. The `rewrites` entry handles the SPA routing (same as the `/*` redirect in your netlify.toml).

Your final repo root should look like:
```
api/
  claude.js        ← renamed from claude.mjs
src/
public/
api/
vercel.json        ← new
package.json
vite.config.js
index.html